circumstances.circumstancesOfRecovery: 81 year old male who died at home from natural causes. Next of kin search proved unsuccessful.
66 year old female who died from natural causes at home.

81 year old male found dead of apparent natural causes in his locked and secure residence during a welfare check. An extensive next of kin search was conducted and no living relatives were located. The subject's case was referred to the Indigent Veteran Program and he was interred at Willamette National Cemetery in Portland, Oregon. His personal property was transferred to the Oregon Division of State Lands and they continued to search for family.

48 year old male who died in a local hospital. The subject reportedly never married, nor did he have children. He and his siblings reportedly were wards of Washington State and they all were subsequently separated. The names of the siblings are unknown.
Reportedly transient male who died in a long-term specialty hospital. Family unknown.

64 year old female found dead at home of natural causes. Her parents pre-deceased the subject. She was divorced and had no children. Her ex-husband reported a sister, Diane L. Jones, as the only surviving family. Multiple attempts to locate Mrs. Jones failed.

74 year old male found dead at home from natural causes. While still alive, the subject and a case worker attempted to obtain a copy of his birth certificate from the San Carlos Reservation, however, given that he was born in the 1930s, there was no paper trail. Family information is unknown.
Natural death of an elderly gentleman. No known family per his social worker.
Natural death of an elderly male. Advised my longtime neighbors and caseworkers that he had family "back East". Names of family, place of birth, etc... are unknown.

59 year old male found dead at home. Longtime friends believe that he was originally from Michigan and that his mother (Carol) might still be alive. Attempts to locate family have thus far been unsuccessful.
72 year old male found dead at home from natural causes. The subject was originally from Croatia and attempts to locate family through diplomatic channels failed.
77 year old female who reportedly was from Missouri originally. The subject reportedly never married. Efforts to locate a sister, Betty (surname unknown), have been unsuccessful.
62 year old male found dead in his home of apparent natural causes. An extensive search for family proved unsuccessful.

52 year old male found dead in his locked and secure apartment during a welfare check. An extensive next of kin search failed to locate the subject's family. The ME's Office was advised by friends of the subject that he was previously homeless, estranged from his family and that his father pre-deceased the subject. The decedent had been active with a local church and the pastor at the church made multiple efforts to locate the subject's mother, Ruth Alford Jones, prior to the subject's death. The church made funeral arrangements for the subject with Rose City Funeral Home in Portland, OR.
